    end
    stat at 27,16 element Object cycle 3 p1 cp437:0x02 under Empty color 0x00
    oop
@collins
#end
:touch
#play tcf
COLUMBIA, HOUSTON. You are three days from home.
The tiny sphere of Earth swells in the window.
$-- Midcourse Correction --
Nudge the burn just so, or you miss the corridor.
!burn;Fire the correction burn.
!jettison;Jettison the service module.
!hold;Hold. Drift a while and look at the Earth.
#end
:burn
#play tefgab
Attitude thrusters bark. A gentle shove.
The trajectory needle settles into the green.
#set corrected
Correction complete. Now shed the dead weight.
#end
:jettison
#if corrected okgo
#play t-c-c
Not yet. Correct your course before you cut loose.
Sever the module now and you fly home blind.
#end
:okgo
#play tfc-fc-c
Explosive bolts fire. The service module
tumbles away, silent, into the dark.
COLUMBIA is a lone cone now, headed for home.
The reentry corridor lies to the east.
#zap touch
#end
:hold
#play t.c.e.g
The Earth turns below, blue and small and far.
You could watch it forever. You won't.
#end

    end
  end
end

